# News posts

## Folder layout

```
News/YYYY/MM/DD/
  content.md    # body (headings, posted date footer)
  index.md      # page wrapper + frontmatter + include content
```

Example `content.md` ends with:

```markdown
###### Posted: 2026-06-10
```

Example `index.md`:

```markdown
---
image:
  path: /images/Excelsior-logo.png
  type: image/png
  alt: Excelsior Fencing Club
description: Short summary for SEO
site_name: Excelsior Fencing Club
title: Same as headline
---

{% include_relative content.md %}
```

## After creating a post

1. Add to **top** of repo root `index.md` (homepage teaser):

   ```markdown
   [link](News/2026/06/10/)
   {% include_relative News/2026/06/10/content.md %}
   ---
   ```

2. Add to **top** of `News.md` (archive) the same way.

## Git workflow

Feature branches often named by post date (e.g. `2026-06-10`). Merge to `main` to publish via GitHub Pages.

Match tone and formatting of neighbouring posts in the same month.
